Former Sports PS Richard Ekai together with the then Rio Games Chief De Mission Stephen Soi and the National Olympic Committee of Kenya Secretary General Francis Kinyili have denied graft charges arising from the Ksh.55 million Rio Olympics scandal. While appearing before Chief Magistrate Douglas Ogoti, the trio faced six counts of abuse of office and four counts of willful failure to comply with the law relating to the management of public funds. They have been freed on a cash bail of sh1m each. 